I would've preferred that the white woman was the protagonist in this film similar to the first one as it brought up some very important themes and interesting metaphors regarding the topics that the original film covered. Also I greatly enjoyed the chemistry and "relationship" between the characters portrayed by Tony Todd and Virginia Madsen.
I don't want this remake to veer too far off from the original in terms of plot and especially characters. I'm hopeful that this remake will be a decent film at least although I don't feel like this version will surpass the quality of the original.
